        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:35AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 434 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Montvale, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bedford...
Montvale...
Big Island...
Forest...
Goode...
Peaks Of Otter Summit...
and Peaks Of Otter Recreation Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
